    • Class fr.sos.witchhunt.view.gui.scenes.ChoiceButton

      class ChoiceButton extends JButton implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • bgColor
          Color bgColor
          The current default background color for this button. For a JButton's default background color, set to null.
        • colorChangeManager
          MouseListener colorChangeManager
          The MouseListener in charge of controlling the Button's style on hover, pressed and exited. Not in charge of collecting any input from the button, for that, see ChoicesPanelController. ChoiceButton.setTheme(Color)
        • defaultBorder
          Border defaultBorder
          The current default border for this button. For a a JButton's default Border, set to null.
        • hoverBorder
          Border hoverBorder
          The current hover border for this button. For a a JButton's default hover Border, set to null.
        • hoverColor
          Color hoverColor
          The current hover color for this button. For a a JButton's default hover color, set to null.
        • insets
          Insets insets
          The buttons internal margins. Modified when rendered by a ChoicesPanel, for a normalized width equal to that of the largest button.
          See Also:
          • ChoicesPanel.renderActionButtons()
        • pressedBorder
          Border pressedBorder
          The border to display around the button when it is pressed. For a a JButton's default hover border, set to null.

    • Class fr.sos.witchhunt.view.gui.scenes.matchsetup.MatchSetupPanel

      class MatchSetupPanel extends JPanel implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • activePCP
          PlayerCreatorPanel activePCP

          A reference to the active PlayerCreatorPanel, the one that could create a player who doesn't exist yet.

        • changed
          boolean changed
        • inputMediator
          InputMediator inputMediator

          The instance of InputMediator in charge of sending input requests to this object.

          Collects input on the active PlayerCreatorPanels using a PlayerCreatorController in order to create players using the GUI.

          See Also:
          • InputMediator
          • ConcreteInputMediator.createPlayer(int, java.util.List, boolean)
          • PlayerCreatorPanel
          • PlayerCreatorController
        • insetsSize
          int insetsSize
          Inner margins for this scene's frame.
        • instructionsLabel
          JLabel instructionsLabel

          The JLabel displaying instructions to follow for creating players.

          Placed at the top.

        • playerCreators
          JPanel playerCreators

          This JPanel will contain the PlayerCreatorPanels instantiated by this object.

          .

          It is placed at the center of the scene, of which it is the largest graphical component.

        • playersAddedButton
          JButton playersAddedButton

          The JButton allowing to validate the match settings and start the match.

          Has no effect while the minimum of players has not been reached.

          Placed at the bottom of the scene.

        • tabletop
          Tabletop tabletop
          The instance of Tabletop this view is a representation of. Used to keep the track of the players creation process. All concurrent views that are able to create players should be synchronized on its basis.
